}

Finding: SQL Injection in /api/search?q= parameter
Code: db.query("SELECT * FROM products WHERE name LIKE '%" + req.query.q + "%'");
Context: Express.js app behind Cloudflare WAF, parameterized queries used elsewhere

Finding: Stored XSS in comment field
Code: commentDiv.innerHTML = comment.body;
Context: Comments sanitized with DOMPurify on input but rendered raw from database. Admin panel displays comments without sanitization.

Finding: SSRF via webhook URL parameter
Code: const resp = await fetch(req.body.webhookUrl);
Context: User-supplied webhook URL fetched server-side. No URL validation. App runs in AWS VPC with metadata endpoint at 169.254.169.254.

Before:
  commentDiv.innerHTML = comment.text;

After:
  commentDiv.textContent = comment.text;

Context: Fix for stored XSS in user comments. Comments support markdown formatting that is now broken by the fix.

Before:
  db.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id=" + req.params.id);

After:
  db.query("SELECT * FROM users WHERE id=$1", [req.params.id]);

Context: Only this one endpoint was fixed. 3 other endpoints in the same file use similar string concatenation.
